710596f-b.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 19th Street
710596f-b.text:
11th Avenue, east side, from W. 19th to 20th Streets, showing
the one story Government Cantonment identified as the New York County
Chapter of the Red Cross. This is at the N. E. corner of 19th Street.
Vtew 2 shows the one story taxpayer (restaurant) at the S. E.
corner of W. 20th Street. This site will be cleared for the new
Seamen's House of the Y. M. C. A.
April 3, 1929
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
